.TH SENTINELBOX 1 "May 2026" "SentinelBox 0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sentinelbox \- secure sandbox for AI-generated code with semantic feedback

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sentinelbox
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \-\- \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sentinelbox
is a rootless, namespace-based sandbox that executes untrusted code
(typically generated by an AI agent) under strict isolation:
PID/Mount/Network/User namespaces, an OverlayFS-on-tmpfs writable layer,
cgroup v2 resource caps, capability dropping, and seccomp
SECCOMP_RET_USER_NOTIF syscall interception.

Blocked syscalls are translated into natural-language
\fIsemantic feedback\fR via the bundled Rust monitor
.RB ( sentinelbox-monitor ),
allowing an AI agent to understand \fIwhy\fR its code failed and how to
repair it within the sandbox's security policy.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-profile=\fINAME\fR
Apply
.IR profiles/NAME .json.
Default:
.IR strict .
Built-in profiles:
.IR strict ,
.IR datascience ,
.IR web .

.TP
.BR \-\-profile\-dir=\fIDIR\fR
Directory holding profile JSON files. Default:
.IR ./profiles .

.TP
.BR \-\-rootfs=\fIPATH\fR
Required. Read-only base rootfs used as the OverlayFS
.IR lowerdir .
Typically created by
.BR setup_rootfs.sh (1).

.TP
.BR \-\-monitor=\fIPATH\fR
Path to the
.B sentinelbox-monitor
Rust binary. Default:
.IR ./monitor/target/release/sentinelbox-monitor .

.TP
.BR \-\-cgroup\-parent=\fIPATH\fR
Parent cgroup under which the per-execution cgroup is created.
Default:
.IR /sys/fs/cgroup .
For unprivileged usage, point this at the user's delegated subtree
(see
.BR setup_cgroup.sh (1)).

.TP
.BR \-\-no\-monitor
Disable launching the Rust monitor.
.B NOTIFY
actions in profile rules degrade to
.B ERRNO=EPERM
when no monitor is attached.

.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging on stderr.

.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print built-in help.

.SH PROFILE FORMAT
Each profile is a JSON document with:
.TP
.B name
Profile identifier.
.TP
.B default_action
One of
.IR ALLOW ,
.IR ERRNO ,
.IR NOTIFY ,
.IR KILL .
Applied to syscalls without explicit rules.
.TP
.B syscall_rules
Array of
.IR {name, action[, errno]} .
.TP
.B resources
Object with
.IR mem_limit_bytes ,
.IR cpu_max_quota ,
.IR cpu_max_period ,
.IR pids_max .
.TP
.B network
Object with
.IR allow ,
.IR allow_dns .

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SENTINELBOX_LOG
Sets the tracing-subscriber filter for the Rust monitor
(e.g.
.IR debug ).
.TP
.B SENTINELBOX_DB
Path to the audit log SQLite DB. Default:
.IR ./sentinelbox.db .

.SH EXAMPLES
Run a shell snippet under the
.I strict
profile:

.RS
.B sentinelbox --profile=strict --rootfs=./rootfs/busybox -- /bin/sh -c "echo hi"
.RE

Run a Python script with relaxed memory limits:

.RS
.B sentinelbox --profile=datascience --rootfs=./rootfs/ds -- python /work/train.py
.RE

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ./profiles/*.json
Built-in security profiles.
.TP
.I ./sentinelbox.db
Default audit log (SQLite WAL).

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Sandboxed program exited normally with status 0.
.TP
.B 127
Sandbox setup failed before the target could be exec'd.
.TP
.B 137
Sandboxed program killed (SIGKILL); typically a KILL-action profile rule.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR seccomp (2),
.BR user_namespaces (7),
.BR cgroups (7),
.BR pivot_root (2)

